title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1980-10-13
lineage: CDR > MacBook using Xact to create flac files, no other work has been done on this recording
description:
Set 1

On The Road Again, Bird Song, El Paso, To Lay Me Down, Heaven Help The Fool, Jack A Roe, The Race is On, Deep Elem Blues-> Ripple

Set 2

Sugaree-> Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, CC Rider, Big Railroad Blues, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Deal

Set 3

Cold Rain & Snow, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> He's Gone-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Casey Jones

First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text:
finally We finally get the entire show to listen to even if broken up at times. all these years later we are so spoiled by the internet archives that sometimes we get picky. I am one that is as picky as anyone, that said this is nice to finally be able to listen to in it's entirety.   
gets 4 stars because has good sound and almost every note.  
Love the long long do we do we not do Sampson.  listen to when they finally do break into it. we go crazy
